  <Fragment slot="methodology">
    <section>
      <h2 id="how-we-evaluate">How we evaluate</h2>
      <p>We score every grinder against five practical criteria: cup quality potential, adjustment precision, workflow speed, retention/static behavior, and maintenance burden. For espresso readers, we weight adjustment precision and repeatability more heavily because tiny setting changes can shift extraction fast. We also compare how a grinder behaves during normal weekday use, since most home users care about consistency under routine pressure.</p>
      <p>Our process is research and comparison based. We synthesize manufacturer specifications, buyer pattern signals, and long-term owner feedback themes. This helps us surface where each model tends to work best: fast hopper workflows, single-dose clarity-first setups, quiet shared-home use, or manual low-retention travel setups.</p>
    </section>
  </Fragment>

