      <p>DF64 Gen 2 hits the strongest balance for most home espresso users who want clear shot improvements without stepping into ultra-premium grinder pricing. The 64 mm flat burr format gives better clarity and separation than many entry conical options, while the stepless collar makes tiny shot-time corrections easier when beans age through the week.</p>
      <p>Workflow is still simple enough for daily use. You get a single-dose path, low retention behavior with a quick bellows finish, and predictable grind response once you mark your rough espresso zone. If your current grinder feels like guesswork between clicks, DF64 Gen 2 usually feels like a real control upgrade rather than a minor spec bump.</p>
