      <p>Encore ESP is the safest budget recommendation when you need true espresso range but want a machine that stays approachable. The stepped interface is easy to learn, replacement parts are widely available, and the grinder is forgiving enough for beginners pulling their first non-pressurized shots.</p>
      <p>You trade away micro-level precision versus stepless grinders, especially with lighter beans and narrow extraction targets. But for most people building a capable home setup without overspending, Encore ESP keeps the learning curve manageable and still offers enough control to produce clean, balanced espresso once dose and prep are consistent.</p>
      <ProsCons
        pros={[
          'Excellent value for a real espresso-capable grinder.',
          'Beginner-friendly adjustment logic with clear repeatability.',
          'Large support ecosystem and strong long-term serviceability.',
